OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBiggest squeeze for public 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsector pay in 20 years     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Public sector pay for jobs such as NHS 
OL,6, workers, teachers and civil servants   
OL,7, fell further behind price rises in the 
OL,8, three months to February, figures show.
OL,10,FWhile wages rose for public sector     
OL,11,Fworkers, price rises outpaced them     
OL,12,Fmeaning a 3% drop in spending power,   
OL,13,Fthe biggest fall in 20 years.          
OL,15,FIn contrast, an average private sector 
OL,16,Femployee's wage bought 0.5% less.      
OL,18,FThe latest inflation figures show the  
OL,19,Fcost of living is rising at its fastest
OL,20,Fpace for 30 years.                     
